#: ../../03_Image_analysis/Intensity.md:35
msgid "To understand saturation another way, imagine you‚Äôre trying to measure average male height with a 2 meter tape measure. If our sample contains men that are taller than 2 meters, we can‚Äôt tell _how much taller_ than 6 feet they are; they‚Äôre like saturated pixels that exceed the intensity we can detect. This saturation of our measurement tool means we can‚Äôt accurately report average height."
